<HEAD>Boy Survives 15-Floor Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 2-year-old boy plunged 15 floors down a rubbish chute inside a Penang city apartment building but suffered only bruises when he landed on a pile of garbage, a newspaper reported today. The daily <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Straits </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> said that <PERSON> Firdaus </PERSON> <PERSON> Zainal </PERSON> <PERSON> Abidin </PERSON> was playing other children Monday when the youngster's sister told their father the boy was missing. The boy's father, <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cpl </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Zainal </PERSON> <PERSON> Abidin </PERSON> <PERSON> Saad </PERSON>, said he looked everywhere for the boy before noticing the rubbish chute was open, the newspaper reported. <PERSON> Zainal </PERSON> rushed down to the ground floor and found his son face down and crying on top of the rubbish, the newspaper said. He rushed his son to the hospital, where doctors examined him and sent him home, saying he had no injury other than bruises on his forehead and elbow, the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Straits </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> said.
