<HEAD>NY-NJ Border Fight: So What's It About This Time?</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LARRY McSHANE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 They're at it again _ those bickering states who share the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> and a hearty animosity. They've battled over Westway, the Statue of Liberty and the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Giants </ORGANIZATION>. The latest provocation in the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York-New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> border war: a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> tax law, passed in 1987 and discovered just recently, which will tax Jerseyans' <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> income at a rate based on their total income. Translation: If you make $ 25,000 a year in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, and your spouse makes $ 75,000 annually west of the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION>, you're taxed on the $ 25,000 as if you're in the $ 100,000 bracket. Adding insult to usury -LRB- or so say the Jerseyans -RRB-, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> invited irate New Jerseyans to sue and suggested any commuter who did n't like the law could quit `` and leave those jobs for New Yorkers.'' After pulling his foot from his mouth, <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> called <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Kean </PERSON> and apologized. But it was too late to stop angry residents of the Garden State from some nasty Cuomo-bashing. `` His arrogance has infuriated <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jerseyans </LOCATION>,'' said <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> Republican <PERSON> Assemblyman </PERSON> <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Hardwick </PERSON>, who has filed suit on behalf of his state. `` He's supposed to be the compassionate governor? He's made it clear his compassion ends at the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>.'' Agree