<HEAD>Chronology of Recent Salvadoran Events</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Also in Monday AMs report.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Salvador, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a chronology of events in <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>'s history over the past 10 years: _ Oct 15, 1979: A group of reformist military officers overthrows the rightist government of President Gen. <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Humberto </PERSON> <PERSON> Romero </PERSON>. Cols. <PERSON> Adolfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Arnoldo </PERSON> <PERSON> Mejano </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jaime </PERSON> <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Gutierrez </PERSON> install a junta of themselves and three civilians. _ Jan 1, 1980: Civilian junta members resign, including Social Democrat <PERSON> Guillermo </PERSON> <PERSON> Ungo </PERSON>, who claims the government is moving too slowly to improve social conditions. <PERSON> Ungo </PERSON> later becomes a political leader of the guerrillas. _ March 1980: <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Napoleon </PERSON> <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, a Christian Democrat, joins the junta _ March 24, 1980: <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> Archbishop <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Arnulfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Romero </PERSON> is assassinated as he celebrates Mass Linked to the killing is <PERSON> Roberto </PERSON> <PERSON> d'Aubuisson </PERSON>, who the following year founds the rightist <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nationalist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, or Arena. <PERSON> D'Aubuisson </PERSON> denies the charge. _ March 30, 1980: Scores die when gunmen fire on a crowd attending <PERSON> Romero </PERSON>'s funeral _ April 1980: Leftist organizations form the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revolutionary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> to become the political wing of the rebel movement _ Oct 5, 1980: Five rebel groups form the <ORGANIZATION> Farabundo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION>. _ Dec 2, 1980: Four <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> women _ three <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> nuns and a lay worker _ are kidnapped. Their bodies are found in a shallow grave Dec. 4. _ Dec 5, 1980: The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> suspends military and economic aid to <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION> pending determination of those responsible for the killings. Four National Guardsmen ultimately are sentenced to 30 years in prison for the murders. _ Dec 12, 1980: <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> is named the first civilian president of <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION> in 30 years. _ Jan 3, 1981: The president of the <ORGANIZATION> Salvadoran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agrarian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reform </ORGANIZATION> and two <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> labor advisers are killed. _ March 28, 1982: First elections for a <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> Of 60 seats at stake, 24 go to <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION>, 19 to <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> and the remainder to smaller political groups. _ March 25, 1984: <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> and <PERSON> d'Aubuisson </PERSON> finish ahead of four other candidates in the first round of presidential elections Guerrillas boycott and threaten violence. _ May 6, 1984: <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> defeats d'Aubuisson in runoff elections and becomes first civilian president chosen by popular vote in 50 years _ March 31, 1985: Congressional and municipal elections <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION> win 33 of 60 assembly seats. _ March 1988: <ORGANIZATION> Congressional </ORGANIZATION> and municipal elections <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> takes 32 of 60 congressional seats. _ June 1988: <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> is found to have terminal liver cancer _ Jan 24, 1989: The guerrillas offer to participate in the presidential election and abide by the results if it is postponed from March 19 until September and security and anti-fraud conditions are adopted. The rebels withdraw the proposal after discussions with the political parties fail to achieve progress.
