> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Station </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Okinawa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, the officials said. The helicopter involved in the crash Friday was assigned to the 13th Marine Expeditionary Unit, also based at <LOCATION> Camp </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pendleton </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> has about 43,000 troops based in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> under a mutual defense treaty. About 30,000 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> troops from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and other parts of <LOCATION> Asia </LOCATION> are in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> to take part in the maneuvers.
