r for any action committed `` in good faith ... in connection with the prevention or suppression of terrorism in any operational area.'' <PERSON> Harmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruppel </PERSON>, a lawyer representing the <PERSON> Shifidi </PERSON> family, has said there is no evidence <PERSON> Shifidi </PERSON> was a pre-selected target for assassination. He said it appears the soldiers sought to discredit the guerrilla organization and intimidate its supporters by provoking violence at its rally. The <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> ruled <PERSON> Botha </PERSON>'s order was invalid, but did not disclose its reasons. On Dec. 15, it ruled against <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> in a similar case, arguing the president did not present important evidence. <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> had granted immunity to four soldiers accused of beating to death a black man in northern <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> has agreed to begin implementing independence in <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION> on April 1, leading to elections in November. In other developments: _ South African and Namibian officials set up checkpoints Monday to monitor cross-border movements Previously, no identity documents were required when traveling between <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>. _ <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>'s South African-led army Sunday demobilized a battalion made up mostly of troops from the <LOCATION> Bushman </LOCATION> tribe known for its extraordinary tracking skills The Bushmen, part of 201 Battalion, were used to track guerrillas in the rugged bush of northern <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>, where most of the fighting took place.
