s, and <PERSON> Greene </PERSON> said other companies should get a chance to compete for the $ 2 billion in long-distance revenues generated each year from the nation's 1.5 million pay phones. The calls in question are those made by dialing `` 0'' plus the long-distance number and either using an operator to charge the call to a home phone, to make it a collect call or use a credit card. Long-distance carriers pay commissions to the businesses where the pay phones are located. <ORGANIZATION> GSA </ORGANIZATION> said it received $ 399,156 in such commissions in 1988. It said it expects to receive about $ 663,000 for the federal treasury this year because of increases in the commission rate.
