Leftovers-`Good Neighbor. They will move spot tomorrow for Wednesday AMs.
       ^___</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 EDITOR'S NOTE _ In reactors, radiology departments and research labs, workers at the end of the day cast off gloves and other discards whose radioactivity, though relatively mild, requires careful disposal. Now, with federal prodding, states are acting to find new ways of getting rid of mountains of low-level nuclear waste. Associated Press reporters have looked at the leaky legacy and uncertain future of the disposal process. Here, they examine the complexities of dealing with potentially lethal leftovers and how rural Nebraskans reacted to the possibility of a dump site in their midst.
