<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Dissidents said Monday they will fight on to oust President <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> <PERSON> Tae-woo </PERSON>, who indefinitely postponed a promised national referendum on his performance. Hundreds of students threw dozens of firebombs into two police stations in the southern city of <LOCATION> Kwangj </LOCATION>, shouting `` Punish <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> Tae-woo!'' according to the South Korean news agency <ORGANIZATION> Yonhap </ORGANIZATION>. The attack destroyed a police motorcycle and caused other extensive damage, <ORGANIZATION> Yonhap </ORGANIZATION> said. There were no immediate reports of injuries and arrests. <ORGANIZATION> Yonhap </ORGANIZATION> said the students also shouted slogans demanding an end to annual `` Team Sprit'' exercises involving 200,000 South Korean and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> soldiers. The attack came after police sneaked into <ORGANIZATION> Chosun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Kwangju </LOCATION> and removed wall posters denouncing the exercises, <ORGANIZATION> Yonhap </ORGANIZATION> said. Dissidents have accused the exercises of heightening tension on the divided <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> peninsula and hampering unification with communist <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> has introduced broad democratic reforms since winning office in late 1987, but many South Koreans distrust the government because of its ties to the authoritarian regime of former President <PERSON> Chun </PERSON> <PERSON> Doo-hwan </PERSON>. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>'s main dissident alliance, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Movement </ORGANIZATION>, urged <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> to stop `` fooling the people'' with the referendum issue and said the alliance will push for <PERSON> Roh </PERSON>'s resignation <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> pos