taff member for the <ORGANIZATION> Massachusetts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Counsel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, said Sunday that defense lawyers are now examining many of those cases and are likely to file motions for new trials. Where faulty warrants led to arrests and convictions, he said, convicted dealers could go free under a rule that bars evidence obtained through police misconduct. <PERSON> Harvey </PERSON> <PERSON> Silverglate </PERSON>, co-chairman of the 320-member <ORGANIZATION> Massachusetts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Criminal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lawyers </ORGANIZATION>, said the <PERSON> Lewin </PERSON> case has revealed what many lawyers suspected all along. `` Anybody who practices criminal law here can tell you that we have great skepticism about these warrants,'' <PERSON> Silverglate </PERSON> said.
