<HEAD>Bush Names Katz</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> on Monday announced he will nominate <PERSON> Julius </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Katz </PERSON>, a private trade consultant, to be deputy <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> trade representative. <PERSON> Katz </PERSON> has been chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, since 1987. Before that, he was vice president for the <ORGANIZATION> Consltants </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. He was also assistant secretary of state for economic affairs at the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> during the adminstration of former President <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON>, and senior deputry secretary of state for international resources during the administration of former President <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Ford </PERSON>. <PERSON> Katz </PERSON>'s post carries rank of ambassador. He would succeed <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>.
