<HEAD>Passenger Bus Careens Into Ditch, Killing 15</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A passenger bus careened off a roadway and plunged into a 100-foot-deep gulley Monday, killing at least 15 people and injuring 35 others, news reports said. The Excelsior news service said the accident on the <LOCATION> Naucalpan-Toluca </LOCATION> state highway outside <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> occurred about 7:20 a.m. -LRB- 8:30 a.m. EST -RRB-. No other vehicles were involved. The news service quoted rescue officials as saying 15 were confirmed dead. <ORGANIZATION> Nacaulpan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> dispatcher <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> Rangel </PERSON> said many of the 35 wounded suffered serious injuries and were taken to nearby hospitals. Rescue attempts were hampered by the depth of the gulley and faulty rescue equipment, the news service said. More than 30 <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION>, fire department and federal highway police units at midday were still pulling bodies and the injured out of the wreckage, <PERSON> Excelsior </PERSON> said. Surviving passengers reportedly told authorities the bus was traveling very fast when the vehicle left the roadway and plummeted into the ditch. Among those reported killed was the driver. His name was not immediately available. <PERSON> Nacaulpan </PERSON> is in the state of <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> just north of <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>.
