 Island nuclear plant, scene of an accident that damaged the core of a reactor and sent radioactive gases into the air. <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> was told that conditions at the plant were stable, and he urged nearby residents to cooperate if emergency measures became necessary. Five years ago: Recording star <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Gaye </PERSON> was shot to death by his father, <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Gay </PERSON> <PERSON> Sr. </PERSON>, in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. The elder Gay pleaded guilty to voluntary manslaughter, and received probation. One year ago: <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON>, who had portrayed <PERSON> Fibber </PERSON> <PERSON> McGee </PERSON> during radio's golden age, died in <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, at age 91. Today's Birthdays: Actor <PERSON> Toshiro </PERSON> <PERSON> Mifune </PERSON> is 69. Author <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Manchester </PERSON> is 67. Actor <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Grizzard </PERSON> is 61. Actress <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Powell </PERSON> is 60. Actor <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> <PERSON> Jump </PERSON> is 57. Actress <PERSON> Debbie </PERSON> <PERSON> Reynolds </PERSON> is 57. Actor <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Hastings </PERSON> is 55. Actress <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> MacGraw </PERSON> is 51. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Eisenhower </PERSON> is 42. Thought for Today: `` Nobody ever died of laughter.'' _ <PERSON> Max </PERSON> <PERSON> Beerbohm </PERSON>, English critic and essayist -LRB- 1872-1956 -RRB-.
