o try to make it through the maze in record time. Each day, the maze's pathways, which contain <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T advertising posters, are reconstructed into a different configuration, giving students a chance to try several different mazes. `` We estimate, on the average, it will take people between 15 and 20 minutes to complete the maze,'' said <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Pugliese </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION> college market manager, who said those that complete the maze in record time receive T-shirts, beach towels and duffel bags. `` Lots of people are vying for the attention of the college students, and I feel this is a healthy and positive event as compared to some of the things spring break is known for,'' explained <PERSON> Gail </PERSON> <PERSON> Piccirilli </PERSON>, in charge of the college marketing for <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> T </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Basking </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ridge </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, as she led a reporter through the maze. She added, though, she had n't come to <LOCATION> Daytona </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION> as a student. `` My father would n't let me,'' she said. Other companies catering to the student crowd included brewers <PERSON> Anheuser </PERSON> <PERSON> Busch </PERSON>, <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> and Coors and automakers <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION>.
