<SECOND>PM-Poll-Method,0724</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll on Savings and Loans Reached 1,108 Nationwide</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Poll-S&amp;Ls-Method</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 This <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General-Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> poll on savings and loans is based on telephone interviews March 6-15 with 1,108 adults in the continental <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. Phone numbers were selected randomly, and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday. The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample. The poll has a three-point margin of error, meaning that if every adult American were asked the same questions, the results theoretically would be the within three points of the poll's results, 19 times out of 20 The error margin is larger for subgroups _ five points, for example, for those with savings and loan accounts. There are other sources of potential error in polls, including the wording and order of questions. These are the questions and results in this poll; because of rounding, sums may not total 100. 1. Let's consider a few different kinds of places where people can put their savings: banks, <ORGANIZATION> savings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; loan associations, credit unions and money market funds. Please tell me whether you think of each as a safe place to keep your money, or not. a. Banks: Safe: 93 percent. Unsafe: 5. Do n't know or no answer: 2. b. S & amp; Ls: Safe: 53 Unsafe: 36. DK-NA: 11. c. Credit unions: Safe 69 Unsafe 13. DK-NA: 19. d. Money market funds: Safe 58 Unsafe: 16. DK-NA: 27. 2. Do you happen to have money in a savings and loan? Yes: 35. No: 63. DK-NA: 1. 3. -LRB- If yes to 2 -RRB- Are you afraid that you could lose your money in a savings and loan failure? Yes: 33. No: 66. DK-NA: 2. 4. -LRB- If yes to 2 -RRB- Have you held off on adding money to your savings and loan account because of the financial problems some savings and loans are having? Yes: 20. No: 79. DK-NA: 1. 5. -LRB- If yes to 2 -RRB- Have you taken any money out of the savings and loan because of the financial problems some savings and loans are having? Yes: 9. No: 91. DK-NA: 0. 6. -LRB- If no to 5 -RRB- Have you considering doing that? Yes: 22. No: 77. DK-NA: 1. 7. -LRB- If no to 2 -RRB- Have you had money in a savings and loan in the past year? Yes: 8. No: 89. DK-NA: 3. a -LRB- If yes to 7 -RRB- Did you take your money out of the savings and loan because of the financial problems some savings and loans are having? Yes: 31. No: 66. DK-NA: 2. 8. -LRB- If no to 7 -RRB- Are you keeping your money out of savings and loans because of the financial problems some savings and loans are having? Yes: 18. No: 79. DK-NA: 3. 9. The federal insurance fund for savings and loan accounts is not big enough to cover all the savings and loans that are in financial trouble. Where do you think most of the money to cover those accounts should come from _ a fee paid by people who have accounts at the savings and loans, higher insurance premiums paid by the savings and loans themselves, or money from the federal government? Fee: 14. Insurance: 42. Federal: 27. DK-NA: 18. 10. What do you think government should do with failing savings and loan associations _ close them down and pay off their depositors, or provide federal assistance to attract new owners? Close: 29. Assist: 51. DK-NA: 20. 11. What do you think is mainly responsible for the problems in the savings and loan industry - bad management by the savings and loans, a lack of government regulation, fraud by savings and loan managers, or general economic problems? Management: 48. Regulation: 10. Fraud: 11. Economic: 21. DK-NA: 10. 12. Do you think the savings and loans should have more government regulation, or less government regulation, or is the current level of regulation about right? More: 53. Less: 7. Right: 25. DK-NA: 15. 13. Do you think the federal government will come up with a long-term solution to the financial problems of the savings and loans, only a temporary solution, or no solution at all? Long-term: 31. Temporary: 39. None: 19. DK-NA: 12.
