<HEAD>Nuke Plant's Owners Buy Bond For Decommissioning After Low Power</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS 2 grafs after 4th graf, `The owners ..., to UPDATE with
Seabrook operator's comments; ADDS 4 grafs with Gregg seeking to block
tests, NRC hearings to begin.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MICHAEL MOKRZYCKI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Owners of the <LOCATION> Seabrook </LOCATION> nuclear power plant bought a bond Monday to guarantee enough money to decommission the reactor if necessary after tests, a move that could give them their long-sought low-power license. The Nuclear Regulatory Commission, in an unprecedented move, ordered <PERSON> Seabrook </PERSON> owners in December to show they could come up with $ 72 million to tear down and clean up the plant after the low-power tests with radioactive fuel if the plant fails to overcome evacuation-planning and financial obstacles to a commercial license. Opponents have argued that towns in the area could not be safely evacuated in case of a reactor accident. One of the 12 New <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> utilities that own the plant has sought bankruptcy protection becuse of debt associated with the plant. The owners paid $ 8.5 million Monday to <ORGANIZATION> Aetna </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Casualty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Surety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Hartford </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Conn. </LOCATION>, to insure any part of the $ 72 million that the owners could not come up with themselves, said <PERSON> Seabrook </PERSON> spokesman <PERSON> Rob </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>. He said <ORGANIZATION> Aetna </ORGANIZATION> would refund as much as $ 6 million if the plant operates commercially. <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, president of <LOCATION> Seabrook </LOCATION> operator <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hampshire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yankee </ORGANIZATION>, called the bond purchase `` a significant milestone for Seabrook Station.'' `` We have now met all of the -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Nuclear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Regulatory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>'s -RRB- stringent requirements to receive a low-power license and begin important testing of <PERSON> Seabrook </P