 State officials said they plan to request within the next week in bankruptcy court that the testing be stopped. On Tuesday, an <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION> licensing board opens what could be the last round of hearings on the plant's commercial license. The Atomic Safety and <ORGANIZATION> Licensing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> will hold hearings for several months in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> on evacuation plans that <PERSON> Seabrook </PERSON> developed for nearby <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> communities that refuse to cooperate. <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> maintains that no evacuation plans could work for the crowded beaches and communities within <PERSON> Seabrook </PERSON>'s 10-mile emergency-planning zone.
